overview: The user initiated a request for a complete aesthetic overhaul of
  their sleep questionnaire application, aiming for a more polished and engaging
  look. The agent began by thoroughly reviewing the existing CSS and component
  styling, identifying areas that felt generic and lacked a specific theme. The
  core approach involved introducing a calming, sleep-themed color palette with
  deep indigos, purples, and teal accents. Key UI elements like the main form
  layout, progress bar, and navigation buttons were redesigned for better visual
  hierarchy and user experience. The intro section was transformed with a hero
  element and feature cards, replacing simple bullet points. Form components
  such as checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders received significant styling
  updates for a softer, more inviting feel. Additionally, section groupings were
  refined, and the report section was updated to align with the new aesthetic.
  The agent confirmed the changes were successfully compiled and reviewed them
  in the browser to ensure a beautiful and cohesive design, moving the app from
  a "template-driven" look to a professional, trustworthy interface tailored for
  sleep health assessment.
